fix: Vercel Web Interface Guidelines audit — 25 findings cleared

Applied vercel-labs/web-interface-guidelines audit:

Accessibility
- aria-label on icon-only buttons (themeBtn, langBtn)
- aria-label on wallet input (Wallet address or ENS name)
- aria-live=polite on loading message
- :focus-visible global styles
- Removed maximum-scale=5 (preserve user zoom)

Forms
- Input: type=text, autocomplete=off, spellcheck=false,
  autocapitalize=off, inputmode=text
- Placeholder: 0x… or vitalik.eth (curly ellipsis)

Animation
- Replaced 13 occurrences of transition all with explicit property lists
- Added prefers-reduced-motion scroll-behavior guard

Typography
- ... to … in Scanning approvals loading copy
- font-variant-numeric tabular-nums on score-num and stat-box val
- .tnum utility class

Touch and layout
- touch-action manipulation on body
- webkit-tap-highlight-color transparent
- overscroll-behavior-y none
- env(safe-area-inset) padding
- viewport viewport-fit cover

Dark mode and theming
- color-scheme dark on html
- meta theme-color per-mode dark and light
- Removed legacy single theme-color tag

Navigation and i18n
- scroll-margin-top 80px on section and id elements
- translate no on MimoShield brand (3 occurrences)

